	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Okay, I decided to resolve the SoW vs. Selos argument once and for all, and went researching for the ACTUAL FORMULAS!!!<BR>
<BR>
Note: Yes, I am a Bard, but the only reason I am studied this is because I wanted to prove my point so that I didnt have to STOP all the time when leading a party. I will be supporting SoW after this, dont worry... here we go:<BR>
<BR>
SoW: 30+(level/2)<BR>
Selos (no drum) 15+level<BR>
Selos (with regular hand drum) 26 + (level*1.8)<BR>
<BR>
there you go... the fight is over.<BR>
<BR>
so, lets use some lvls:<BR>
level 10:<BR>
SoW=35<BR>
Selos no drum=20<BR>
Selos regular drum=44<BR>
level 20:<BR>
SoW=40<BR>
Selos no drum=35<BR>
Selos regular drum=62<BR>
level 30<BR>
SoW=45<BR>
Selos no drum=45<BR>
Selos regular drum=80<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
so, there we go. At level 30, SoW and selos sung are equal, yet with a REGULAR HAND DRUM Selos wins, hands down.<BR>
<BR>
Now, please remember that those are just numbers, too. We bards have a major drawback, in that it only helps our party if they stay close (and that is what matters, since IMHO bards are group-oriented, and not a great solo class... we can do it, but it is waaaaay toooo sloooow).<BR>
<BR>
Also, selos CANNOT BE SUNG INDOORS (dungeons, caves, etc)... now, SoW cannot be cast indoors, but it CAN be active while indoors (if it runs out, U gotta zone outside to recast it, though)<BR>
<BR>
so... Bards are faster (who sings Selos without their drum??? anyone???), but SoW is better in many circumstances. Give the main puller SoW, so the bard can be singing other songs.<BR>
<BR>
Verant made Selos faster, yet SoW more versatile for a reason: GAME BALANCE!!!<BR>
<BR>
Thank you, and happy hunting<BR>
<BR>
-Luzienne Riverstorm<BR>
24 Bard<BR>
Tarew Marr<BR>
Whisper of Death, Bard Advisor<BR>
<BR>
ps: ask Druids for SoW nicely! It is not their job to SoW you, but many are &quot;Nice&quot; enough to do so... be courteous!!! 
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
