	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				A lot of what the two people above me have said is true, and is very, very obvious.  I, a level 9 druid, havee been asked for SoW many a time meanwhile meditating.  I find it funny, so I don't take it in offense.  If and when I turn level 14 and get SoW, the first thing I'm doing is treeforming myself at the Kelethin Bank and buffing everyone up for no apparent reason.  I've been doing it for quite some time now, and it's pretty fun, knowing that you've just helped someone out.  Not once has someone come to me and just rudely demanded SoW from me.  Ever.  So, if they put in the effort to try to be sincere, be nice, and perform an act of kindness.  Also, try just buffing or healing someone who needs it, or just at random.  It's really cool, and more often than not, you get a &quot;faction raise&quot; with your fellow players, and some money or a favor off of it.  I even got clarity for buffing and helping out a guy in need!  So, random acts of kindness, like giving it away, are something that maybe you should consider.  It enhances your reputation, ahem, Bansheea, and people know that you're a nice guy, which makes it easier to get into groups.  I have a quite a few friends that I have helped, and have quite a bit gotten into a group that would've been deaf to my questions had I not been nice to them.  So, if you can manage it, try being nice and buffing or healing someone who needs it, or at random!  The results will surprise you!
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
